-- Adidas to consolidate US operations
-- 
-- Thu Apr 5, 2007 5:02pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/05/us-adidas-reorganization-idUSWNAS577620070405

 

 (Reuters) - Adidas AG ADSG.DE said it will consolidate its Adidas and Reebok U.S. apparel and footwear distribution centers into new facilities in Spartanburg, South Carolina by fall 2009, affecting about 375 employees. 

 The facilities in Memphis, Tennessee and Hebron, Kentucky are expected to remain in operation until fall 2008 and those at Stoughton and Norwood, Massachusetts and an existing Spartanburg facility are expected to remain in operation until fall 2009. The affected employees belong to the company's apparel distribution facilities in Memphis and Hebron, and at footwear distribution facilities in Stoughton and Norwood, the company said in a statement. Adidas employees currently in Spartanburg will move to the new site a few miles away, it said. (Reporting by Anup Roy in Bangalore)